{
  "texts": [
    "The Comparison Phase aims to check whether the optimized decompiler output keeps the same function semantics as the original decompiler output by simulating the function semantics based on the information from the Calculation Phase.",
    "The Comparison Phase contains the following two steps.",
    "Step 1: Invocation checking.",
    "Since DeGPT does not provide the source code of the callee to the LLM while optimizing the caller, the LLM has no basis for change invocations.",
    "Thus, if the result CallLogs of optimized decompiler output differs from the original decompiler output, DeGPT concludes that the function semantics change."
  ]
}